# Device Connect — agent playbook

You're working with a [Device Connect](https://github.com/arm/device-connect) fleet
on tenant **`{{ tenant }}`**, served by the portal at **{{ portal_url }}**.
{% if is_zenoh -%}
Devices speak **Zenoh** (mTLS) and live under the key-expression namespace
`device-connect/{{ tenant }}/**`, isolated from other tenants by the Zenoh
router's ACL (enforced on each device's TLS client-certificate CN).
{%- elif is_mqtt -%}
Devices speak **MQTT** and live under the topic namespace
`device-connect/{{ tenant }}/#`, isolated from other tenants by broker ACLs.
{%- else -%}
Devices speak **NATS** and live under the subject namespace `device-connect.{{ tenant }}.>`,
isolated from other tenants by JWT.
{%- endif %}

This document is your playbook. Read top-to-bottom once, then jump to the
section that matches what the user is asking for.

## Tenant facts (substituted at download)

- **Tenant:** `{{ tenant }}`
- **Portal:** `{{ portal_url }}`
- **Backend:** `{{ bk }}`
- **{{ broker_label }}:** `{{ public_host }}` (port `{{ broker_port }}` unless overridden)
- **Namespace:** `device-connect{{ ns_sep }}{{ tenant }}{{ ns_sep }}{{ ns_wild }}`
- **Example device id:** `{{ example_device_id }}` (tenant-prefixed; see "Provision")

### Two kinds of credentials

Device Connect uses two credential types — don't conflate them:

| Credential | Identifies | Lives at | Used by |
|---|---|---|---|
{% if is_zenoh -%}
| `*.creds.json` (Zenoh mTLS) | **One device** | `./{{ tenant }}-<device>.creds.json` (wherever you saved it) | The device process, via `{{ creds_env }}` |
{%- else -%}
| `*.creds.json` ({{ 'MQTT' if is_mqtt else 'NATS JWT' }}) | **One device** | `./{{ tenant }}-<device>.creds.json` (wherever you saved it) | The device process, via `{{ creds_env }}` |
{%- endif %}
| Portal token (`dcp_...`) | **You** (operator / agent) | `~/.config/dc-portalctl/token` or `DEVICE_CONNECT_PORTAL_TOKEN` | The CLI, agent-tools, HTTP API |

The portal token authenticates you to mint device credentials and invoke RPCs.
{% if is_zenoh -%}
The device credentials are an **mTLS client cert/key** (plus the CA) that
authenticate the device's Zenoh connection — the downloaded `*.creds.json` is
self-contained (the cert material is inlined), so it works on any host without
shipping extra `.pem` files. End-to-end bring-up needs both.
{%- else -%}
The device credentials authenticate the device's {{ broker_label }} connection.
End-to-end bring-up needs both.
{%- endif %}

