## Appendix A: HTTP API reference

The CLI is the recommended path; this exists for sandboxes that block venvs or
for automation that prefers raw HTTP. All endpoints expect
`Authorization: Bearer $DEVICE_CONNECT_PORTAL_TOKEN`. Replace
`{{ portal_url }}` with your tenant's portal URL.

```bash
# Discover
GET  /api/agent/v1/fleet
GET  /api/agent/v1/devices?device_type=camera&location=warehouse1
GET  /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}/capabilities
GET  /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}/functions

# Provision (devices:provision scope)
POST /api/agent/v1/devices
     {"device_name":"cam-001","device_type":"camera","location":"warehouse1/loading-dock"}

# Decommission / rotate (devices:provision / devices:credentials scope)
# ⚠ Both currently return HTTP 501 `not_implemented` on every bundled backend
# (no backend implements remove_device / rotate_device_credentials yet).
# See Section 3 for the workaround. Endpoints are listed for completeness:
DELETE /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}
POST   /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}/credentials:rotate

# Invoke (devices:invoke scope)
POST /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}/invoke
     {"function":"capture_frame","params":{...},"reason":"..."}

# Stream events (events:read scope) — must specify duration|count|follow
GET  /api/agent/v1/devices/{id}/events/{event_name}/stream?duration=30&count=5&format=ndjson
```

Worked example:

```bash
curl -X POST \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $DEVICE_CONNECT_PORTAL_TOKEN" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"function":"capture_frame","params":{"resolution":"4k"},"reason":"Daily inspection","timeout":10}' \
    {{ portal_url }}/api/agent/v1/devices/{{ example_device_id }}/invoke
```

