## Appendix B: systemd deployment

For longer-lived deployments, prefer a systemd-user unit so the service
auto-restarts on crash and on reboot.

The `ExecStart` here points at the venv interpreter from Section 6
(`~/.dc-edge/bin/python`), not `/usr/bin/python3`. On hosts where the
default `python3` resolves to Homebrew, pyenv, or anything other than
`/usr/bin/python3`, hard-coding `/usr/bin/python3` runs an interpreter
that doesn't see the install — the unit fails with `ModuleNotFoundError:
No module named 'device_connect_edge'`. Pinning to the venv avoids that.

```ini
# ~/.config/systemd/user/dc-cam-001.service
[Service]
WorkingDirectory=%h/dc
Environment={{ creds_env }}=%h/dc/{{ tenant }}-cam-001.creds.json
{% if is_mqtt -%}
Environment=MQTT_URL=mqtt://{{ public_host }}:{{ broker_port }}
{%- elif not is_zenoh -%}
Environment=NATS_URL=nats://{{ public_host }}:{{ broker_port }}
{%- endif %}
ExecStart=%h/.dc-edge/bin/python %h/dc/my_device.py
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

```bash
ssh user@edge-host "systemctl --user daemon-reload && \
                    systemctl --user enable --now dc-cam-001"

# Tail logs
ssh user@edge-host "journalctl --user -u dc-cam-001 -f"

# Pull recent logs back without leaving a shell open
ssh user@edge-host "journalctl --user -u dc-cam-001 --since '10 min ago'" \
    > /tmp/dc-cam-001.log
```

To survive reboot when the user isn't logged in, also enable lingering on the
edge host: `sudo loginctl enable-linger $USER`.
